<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-06-08T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-06-08T15:00:00-05:00" n="951" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d951">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 860d.00/164</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Francis</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-06-08T16:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">June 8,
                                            1918, 4 p.m.</hi></date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>168. Your 209, May 27, 5 p.m. Department has not changed policy
                                regarding Finland, and is not prepared to recognize independence or
                                to ship foodstuffs. Department has noted continued presence of
                                German troops in Finnish territory and their reported activities in
                                Karelia.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed><persName corresp="#p_PFL1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi></persName></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>